{
  "texts": [
    "A supersector is an open interval obtained from a singular sector by enlarging it by π 2k on both sides.",
    "The preferred isomorphism (3) locally around θ can be extended to the singular sector containing θ and even the associated supersector.",
    "In general, a small interval S can be part of different supersectors, yielding different isomorphisms of the form (3) on S, all coming from preferred splittings for some θ.",
    "However, if an interval S ⊂ ∂ is large enough, one has a unique choice for such a splitting valid on the whole of S, as the following lemma shows.",
    "Then there is a unique supersector containing S and the midpoint of S lies in the associated singular sector."
  ]
}